article.headline: O'Grady scores 17 fro Marquette
article.linkText: Golden Eagles eye, then beat Blue Demons
article.story:
FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Katie O'Grady scored 17 points for
Marquette, which beat (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP) DePaul 74-70 Friday in the quarterfinals of the Conference USA tournament.

Carolyn Kieger added 16 points for the Golden Eagles (21-8).

Crystal Weaver's jump shot with about 2 minutes to play gave
Marquette a 67-66 lead. The Golden Eagles stretched the advantage
to 69-66 on two free throws by O'Grady.

Charlene Smith, who led DePaul (22-6) with 20 points, cut the
deficit to 69-68 with 43 seconds left. But Kieger responded with a
jumper to push the lead to 71-68.

DePaul managed only one more basket and lost to Marquette for
the second time in six days. Ashley Luke added 16 points for the
Blue Demons .

Marquette faces No. 11 Houston in the semifinals Saturday. The
Lady Cougars beat Cincinnati 84-67 Friday.
